## The Rules of Hooks

1. **Only call hooks at the top level** ‚Äî not inside loops, conditions, or nested functions
2. **Only call hooks from React functions** ‚Äî components or custom hooks (functions starting with `use`)

## Why These Rules Exist

React tracks hooks by the order they're called. If the order changes between renders, React can't match state to the correct hook.

```
First render:  useState(0) ‚Üí useEffect(...) ‚Üí useMemo(...)
Second render: useState(0) ‚Üí useMemo(...)    // üí• Order changed!
```

## Fix

### ‚ùå Problem: Conditional Hook Call

```jsx
function Profile({ user }) {
  // üí• Hook called conditionally
  if (user) {
    const [name, setName] = useState(user.name);
  }

  return <div>{user?.name}</div>;
}
```

### ‚úÖ Solution: Call Hook Unconditionally, Conditionally Use Result

```jsx
function Profile({ user }) {
  // ‚úÖ Always called
  const [name, setName] = useState(user?.name ?? '');

  if (!user) return <div>No user</div>;

  return <div>{name}</div>;
}
```

### ‚ùå Problem: Hook Inside Loop

```jsx
function ItemList({ items }) {
  // üí• Different number of hooks each render
  items.forEach(item => {
    const [selected, setSelected] = useState(false);
  });

  return <div>{/* ... */}</div>;
}
```

### ‚úÖ Solution: Move to Child Component

```jsx
function ItemList({ items }) {
  return (
    <div>
      {items.map(item => (
        <Item key={item.id} item={item} />
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}

function Item({ item }) {
  // ‚úÖ Each Item has its own hook instance
  const [selected, setSelected] = useState(false);
  return <div onClick={() => setSelected(!selected)}>{item.name}</div>;
}
```

### ‚ùå Problem: Hook After Early Return

```jsx
function UserData({ userId }) {
  if (!userId) {
    return <div>No user ID</div>; // üí• Hooks below won't be called
  }

  const [user, setUser] = useState(null);

  useEffect(() => {
    fetchUser(userId).then(setUser);
  }, [userId]);

  return <div>{user?.name}</div>;
}
```

### ‚úÖ Solution: Hooks Before Any Returns

```jsx
function UserData({ userId }) {
  const [user, setUser] = useState(null);

  useEffect(() => {
    if (userId) {
      fetchUser(userId).then(setUser);
    }
  }, [userId]);

  // ‚úÖ Early return after all hooks
  if (!userId) {
    return <div>No user ID</div>;
  }

  return <div>{user?.name}</div>;
}
```

